text: Underwater Observatory Marine Park Eilat () is a park, conservation centre and aquarium in Eilat, Israel. It also has an underwater observatory in the Red Sea. It is located at the south of Eilat's Coral Beach Nature Reserve. It was founded in 1974 and was the first of its kind in Israel. It is the biggest public aquarium in Israel, and it has over 800 species. == Other websites == * Coral World Category:Theme parks in Israel Category:Museums in Israel Category:Eilat
